# skill-corpus-merge-consolidation-workflow — History

## v2.1.0 (2026-06-14)

**Changed by:** Post-drain closure audit workflow (2026-06-14 myrmidon-merge-triage session)
**Verification:** verified-ci
**Previous version:** v2.0.0

### What changed

- **Added Part F — Post-Drain Closure Audit**: New workflow section covering the mandatory
  companion step after any mass PR drain that closes PRs as "superseded." Includes quick
  reference commands, a step-by-step audit procedure, skill-family partition strategy,
  COVERED/PARTIAL/LOST verdict rules, salvage PR creation pattern, an observed over-close
  rate table (~26%), and carrier PR risk documentation.
- **Added trigger (9) to description**: "a mass PR drain or consolidation has closed PRs as
  superseded and you need to audit for silently-dropped unique content."
- **Added 5 new Failed Attempts rows** documenting: trusting drain-agent verdicts without
  audit, one-agent-per-PR (instead of per-cluster) audit strategy, judging COVERED by version
  number rather than content, and assuming ADD-new-skill closures are safe without verifying
  the target file exists on main.
- **Added tags**: `salvage-audit`, `closed-pr`, `post-drain`.
- **Added Verified On row** for the 2026-06-14 audit (38 closed PRs, 10 with dropped content,
  5 salvage PRs #2514-#2518 merged).

### Why

A 2026-06-14 audit of 38 PRs closed as "superseded" during a drain pass found a ~26%
over-close rate. One carrier PR (#2346) claimed to absorb 14 siblings but silently dropped 6
of their learnings. A 4-agent swarm partitioned by skill-family was the key efficiency
insight. All 10 dropped-content PRs were recovered via 5 amendment PRs, all merged in CI.
This is a MINOR bump — no existing workflow is changed, only a new Part F workflow added.

---

## v2.0.0 (2026-06-07)

**Changed by:** 2026-06-07 full-corpus consolidation pass (50 clusters)
**Verification:** verified-ci

### What changed

- **Gate 1 now requires a canonical-vs-absorbed collision check (Gate 1b)** in addition to the
  existing absorbed-vs-absorbed check (Gate 1a). Flags any cluster whose `canonical_name` appears
  in another cluster's `absorbed_skills`. Added to Quick Reference, the Phase 2 workflow, and a
  Failed Attempts row. Real incident: `markdown-linting-and-build-fixes` was absorbed by the
  mkdocs cluster while another cluster amended it as a canonical → wrong-merge + duplicate PR.
- **Merge helper must run `pre-commit` once and re-stage before the real commit.** The
  `end-of-file-fixer` hook modifies the `.history` on the first commit, aborting it (branch pushed
  with no commit / empty PR number). Added a note in the Phase 3 merge workflow + a Failed
  Attempts row.
- **Do not re-dispatch merge agents by agent/background-task ID during recovery.** Re-dispatching
  for a still-live cluster produced duplicate PRs (#2233 + #2234 on `skill/ruff-specific-rule-fixes`).
  Verify cluster progress from git/gh state (`git ls-remote --heads`, `gh pr list --head`), not
  from notification IDs. Added a Failed Attempts row + Phase 3 note.
- **`update-marketplace.yml` is broken** — it regenerates `marketplace.json` but FAILS at "Open
  PR" because org policy blocks GitHub Actions from creating PRs. Added a manual reconcile section
  (`python3 scripts/generate_marketplace.py` → commit → PR) + a Failed Attempts row.
- Added a **Verified On** row and a **Deduplication Scale Examples** row for the 2026-06-07
  full-corpus pass (518 → 291 skills, -227, -44%).

### Why

A large validated 50-cluster full-corpus consolidation pass (273 absorbed skills, 10 waves of up
to 5 worktree swarm agents) surfaced materially new gate rules and workflow steps. These are
breaking additions to the merge procedure (a new mandatory gate, a re-ordered commit sequence, and
a now-mandatory manual marketplace reconcile), warranting a MAJOR version bump. No existing history
content is removed; the absorbed-skill snapshots below are retained verbatim.

